description: Chased, shot at, beaten and bloody, Zan Jensen has hiked 40 miles across Nepal in a desperate bid to save her partner and claim a treasure worth dying for on the summit of Mount Everest. With her stash exhausted and her dream looming above her, Zan Jensen's arrival at Base Camp will turn the launchpad of a lifelong dream into a bloody battleground.

Being beautiful is never easy, especially if you're an eighteen year old boy like Gene who is constantly mistaken for a girl because of his delicate good looks. Gene is, in fact, anything but delicate. He is the ringleader of a group of tough kids in an all boy's school, and he's quick to beat the living daylights out of anyone who even hints that he resembles a girl.

If that wasn't hard enough for a regular teenage guy to cope with, his life is about to take a shocking turn for the worse. When Gene stumbles upon strange happenings in the forest, he gets sucked into a world of vampire intrigue and sinister romance that he never knew existed. And he learns that there are worse things than being turned into a vampire: being turned into a girl?!
name: Vol. 2

description: Wondrous new cultures and technology await the caravan from Monanti - if Lilli and Petra can deliver them safely from a stampeding dinosaur pack. Meanwhile, General Clawson and the cadets must stop predators from retaking the city.

Having broken into the biggest Hollywood party of 1986, our gang of Sixteen Candles-style teens must now survive what's become a Commie-Coke-Zombie-Bash of epic proportions!

Can they team up with action stars to do battle with the undead icons? Are there enough automatic weapons at their disposal?!
Seren and her companions race across the land to find assistance against the Mad Lord's armies, but soon discover the war is not as simple as they thought.

A nation's capital ravaged by war. As battles between rebel and government forces decimate the surroundings, a foreign spy navigates the destruction on a covert mission. Circumventing and eliminating any obstacles that pose a risk, he must stay alive long enough to accomplish his mission. With a precise plan and ordered mind he steels himself, and looks to the madness of his environment to provide the escape he needs. However, relying on chaos for salvation is not the guide most suited for order.
Alexis Quinn and his team find an unexpected survivor in the ruins of a research hospital.
Markie learns to cope with having powers while Liza juggles homeschooling, friends and family. Meanwhile, a new vigilante stalks the streets of Columbus.
Balthazar and General Adross scout out ahead of Luxuria legion, but are spotted by Baal's elite mercenary generals -- The Dread Furies! -- and are forced to flee for their lives.
In these heart-felt shorts, join the gang as they deal with cat thiefs, card games, and more.

“OUTBREAK,” Part Two

Slacker genius Dr. David Loren made a calculated gamble that the US government would never allow his latest DNA-targeting virus to go airborne… and lost. Can he mitigate the collateral damage triggered by his deadly invention? Or will he lose everyone he loves?
name: Outbreak, Part Two

description: Lex and Cal travel back in time and break up a Skull & Bones ritual in the Tomb at Yale. Meanwhile, Carmot and Vodnar try to rescue the brothers from the W.I.L.D. Machine. Luna makes her cameo appearance with a big bang.

The boys mount a desperate assault, and unleash their revenge. For some, the war ends here. For others, like Johnny Summer, the battle rages on. Who will survive and what will be left of them? Find out in Chapter 4 of the thrilling, critically-acclaimed graphic mini-series WOLVES OF SUMMER.
name: Bullets

description: A dark fantasy drama in a modern setting, Yumiko finds her perfect little life as the merch girl for her boyfriend's band going to Hell - literally. Yumi must help her friends realize they're caught in the middle of an ancient conflict between a god of excess and his jilted lover, before everyone dies as a result of it. This project redefines the possibilities of what comics can do when crossed with music, and is supported by an online animated music video.

volume.name: Yumiko: Curse of the Merch Girl

description: The madness continues as Squid girl tells her bizarre fairytale like story involving secrets in nature. In other worlds Ace journalist Vernon Cutter lands the interview of a lifetime with the enigmatic Iverna Deskerna. Little by little he ventures further into her dark and dangerous world.
name: Feels Like Falling, Chapter 2

volume.name: Hagar the Horrible The Big Bands Are Back!
Haiopeis: Haie wie du und ich

description: Yesterday, Walter tried to kill himself. Today, he wakes up to find that everyone who comes near him suddenly and inexplicably dies. Everyone, that is, except for a mysterious lady named Eliza, who is desperately trying to keep Walter safe from a deadly assassin known as Miller - which would be easy if he didn't keep coming back from the dead without a scratch on him. Learn the true meaning of life and death in AFFLICTION.
name: Chapter One

description: The second AOD series from Dynamite Entertainment is now available as a Collection! Written by James Kuhoric and featuring the artwork of Nick Bradshaw and Sanford Greene Shop 'Til You Drop (Dead) puts Ash back in the real world and the S-Mart but not without a few bumps surprises and Deadites along the way! This collection features the four complete issues of the series and will also include a cover gallery featuring Nick Bradshaw Sanford Greene Eric Ebas Jae Lee Richard Isanove Paolo Rivera and Ale Garza!
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Army of Darkness: Shop Till You Drop Dead

description:
The Army of Darkness features the crossover no one ever expected to see: Army of Darkness vs. Re-Animator! Ash Vs. West! The Ultimate Lovecraftian battle as Herbet West leaps from the literary page to fight Ash! Winner takes all! Ash finds himself committed to Arkham Asylum. It's here that he runs afoul of a rather ghoulish and creepy Herbert West... and the battle of the century begins!

This collection features the four issues of this titanic teaming as well as a complete cover gallery (J.G. Jones, Sanford Greene, Gabriele Dell'Otto, Nick Bradshaw, and more) and a Nick Bradshaw Monster Gallery Sketchbook!
name: TPB

description:
Collects Army of Darkness Vol. 1 5-7 and Tales of Army of Darkness!

Return to the grueling horror of the Army of Darkness movie trilogy with this explosive new collection of the OLD SCHOOL storyline from the Army of Darkness series by writer James Kuhorik and artist Kevin Sharpe!

Plus: this special collection also includes the TALES OF THE Army of Darkness MONSTER SIZED ANNUAL featuring 48 pages of all out horror and action from the Army of Darkness - 5 fantastic and terrible tomes by the following creative teams: Shawn Spurlock and Paul Azaceta, James Kuhoric and Nick Bradshaw Jim Kuhoric and Filip Sablik, Robert Napton and Michael O'Hare...And special guests... Robert Kirkman and...Ryan Ottley!

Also includes a cover gallery from Old School and the Tales Annual!
name: Volume 1

description: Brilliant Boy is a critically-acclaimed all-ages comic about the hilarious adventures of the smartest boy in the town of Baskerville. A series of comic strips were developed based on the Brilliant Boy characters. This book is the collection of those strips.

A Graphic Novel cross between Kurt Vonnegut and a spilled bottle of ink, BROKE tells the story of Regina Kaufmann, an Insurance Investigator under investigation. She's got everything a girl's heart could desire, big car, big screen TV, and one big problem. She's broke. Short on cash with bloodhound bill collectors breathing down her neck, while maneuvering through a cast of peculiar situations, how far will Regina go to maintain her lifestyle of trivial luxuries? BROKE, a satirical look at modern life, which begs the question... is the world broke?
name: GN

description:
COLLECTING THE RETURN TOP COW'S TOP-SELLING SERIES

Carin Taylor, codenamed Velocity, has escaped from the CDI controlled Millennium City and is desperately trying to find the one man she believes can help her prevent the end of the world. When she runs a group of other CDI escapees, will they help her... or turn their backs? Top Cow founder MARC SILVESTRI (THE DARKNESS, Incredible Hulk) returns to his first Image series to bring you a contemporary re-imagining rooted in cutting-edge, real world technology!

Collects CYBERFORCE #1-5.
name: Volume One

description:
CINDERELLA WAS NEVER THIS DASHING!

Otogi Grimm, a far-flung descendant of the renowned Grimm Brothers, has always regarded the fairy tales his ancestors concocted as pure fiction. Now, the introverted half-Japanese teen is about discover that the Grimm legacy is anything but pure.

Otogi finds a manuscript that reveals the dark truth about the Brothers Grimm and the secret deal they made with beings known as the Marchen Demons. With Cinderella as his guide, can Otogi Grimm unlock the power of the manuscript and save himself from a horde of living fairy tales gone wild?
name: Cinderella

description: A new mission begin for Qu-Qu 7 and Ha-Se 12 in a party full of...diamonds! The PIA agents are looking into a mysterious diamond's producer! Will they succeed in stealing his secret?

volume.name: Donald Duck Agent Qu-Qu 7: A Diamond Jam

description: The end could come from any direction. Mega-volcanos. Killer viruses. Asteroids. All that's certain is that the end of humanity is upon us. Join Jack, Cass, and the rest of the Somerset Foundation as they race against the clock to avert extinction-level events. This double issue features BLACK HOLE SON, Parts 1 and 2, and includes 44 pages of story and art plus a bonus section with concept art, sketches, and other behind-the-scenes info! DOOM SOON is slick, sci-fi cool...like Final Destination for the entire human race.

When Howard's father is stricken by an evil alien entity, Howard, Spot and Constable Smith must race to a secret government base in Antarctica to seek out the one man who can save his life: Dr. Herbert West. But the doctor has unwittingly awakened a sinister presence in the frozen wasteland that threatens to enter our world. In the end, one our heroes will be forced to Sacrifice his life to prevent the monstrosity from entering our destroying our planet.
name: Chapter 1

volume.name: Howard Lovecraft and the Kingdom of Madness

description: When Mickey and Goofy found a bunch of lost wallets, it seemed like a simple case of returning them to their rightful owners. That is, until they tried to return the wallet of a certain missing Professor. Once Mickey heard that the Professor had disappeared, he went from good Samaritan to Private Eye. And as usual, when Mickey and Goofy get on a case, they find out there's a lot more to the story than they bargained for!

volume.name: Mickey Mouse and the Case of the Lost Scientists

description: Mickey and Goofy travel back in time to unravel an ancient mystery! At the beginning of the 20th century, a famous and revolutionary plane, the Avion Bleu, disappeared during an international air rally. Where did it go, and how is it connected to one of the biggest robberies of the century? Only Mickey can discover the amazing truth!

volume.name: Mickey Mouse and the Pioneers of Flight

description: Mr. Billingmyer wants nothing more than to make Halloween as special for the children as it's always been for him. But the night takes a frightening and bizarre turn when a home invader darkens the old man's doorway...

person_credits.name: Ryan Sheffield
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: It's a murder mystery on the high seas in a tale from Smitty's sordid past as a pirate! When the first mate is found brutally slain, Smitty's Captain turns to him for answers. But the evidence is misleading, and Smitty's prying into the business of his crewmates will have consequences even he can't envision.

volume.name: Pirate Eye: Murder At Ten Knots
Qui a Besoin de la Lune?

description: The first issue of Real West starts with a bang with a brand new story from writer John Arcudi (B.P.R.D.) and artist A.C. Zamudio!

SONIC SAGA VOL. 4 collects selected stories from Sonic the Hedgehog #129, 177-180.

Sonic's epic adventures aren't just stories-they're SAGAS! Blast into the action at Sonic speed with the continuation of the all-new Sonic Saga graphic novel series! This volume collects a crucial point in the history of Sonic's hometown of New Mobotropolis. After narrowly avoiding annihilation at the hands of Dr. Eggman, the citizens face a bright new future -- one full of change. But change isn't exactly so bright for everyone. Tensions boil over when Sonic does battle with...TAILS?! Brother fights brother, political tensions start to brew, and friends and family are turned against each other. What evils go unchecked during all this infighting?
name: Volume 4

volume.name: Sonic Saga Series: House of Cards

description: It's the 13th century, and the Holy Land is under the rule of two monastic orders. In 1271, as he was about to leave for the Crusades, Argan, a knight hospitaller, was summoned by his master to be given a sword with the fateful name of "Will of God". He was ordered to go on a dangerous mission: to defend, at any cost, the knights' fortress called the Krak, the last bastion of the Jabal Ansariya foothills besieged by the Saracens. But Argan could not know of the trials and tribulations awaiting him, or what he would find in those sacred lands... "May abundance, wisdom and beauty be with you; if you go with pride alone, will sully everything."...
name: The Fall of the Krak

description: Dangerous. Harrowing. Uncompromising. Catch up with the critically-acclaimed 1st arc before the explosive finale shatters all expectations. As a boy soldier, a WEREWOLF, he lived through impossible evil. Years later, this former Hitler Youth forges a bloody path to redemption. Collects WOLVES OF SUMMER Chapters 1-3 Also includes: An exclusive backpage, process pages, a 6 page preview of Chapter 4: Bullets and "Words Can Never Hurt Me", and a 10 page bonus comic by artist Andrew Herbst.
name: Volume One
Auf unbekannter Fahrte ; In den Ketten der Sklavenjager

volume.name: El Hazard: The Magnificent World Volume 3

person_credits.name: Charles M. Schulz
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: No good deed goes unpunished: Katie, a former journalist, and Rupert, a former soldier, struggle with their lives in the years after they both had a brief brush with heroism. When an old nemesis is awakened half a world away, that struggle is about to get a lot more deadly.
Katie and Rupert are framed, and pursued across London, the city with the most CCTV cameras in the world. In a land where everything is observed and recorded, can anywhere be safe?

You know how the internet controls everything? Well, there's an angry and unbalanced consciousness in it and it's mad at Katie and Rupert. And it is taking its anger out on the world. That anger even reaches all the way to rural Wiltshire.

Katie and Rupert are dragged to America, in a desperate attempt to halt Nathaniel's path of mass destruction. They learn several things: don't trust scientists, don't trust generals, and don't trust Stinky's dad.
A western showdown in the high Colorado as Rupert, Stinky and Katie take on General Bowditch's marines... as van Meter slips out a side door and gets a surpise of his own.

It's the end of the line for Rupert, Stinky and Katie, in a dusty Kansas cornfield. A last-minute deal allows them one slim chance at survival, if in their most weakened state ever they can face their greatest enemy ever.

The final chapter of Ashes. Cain and Katie encounter old enemies and new friends on the island of Mustique, a sunny place for shady people. With art from RM Guéra and Bill Sienkiewicz. Written by Alex de Campi.

On the day he entered College, Shingo reencounters his childhood friend Kyou. Shingo always desired to meet him once again, ever since the day Kyou mysteriously left home. He is determined to be accepted and move in where Kyou lives: Fresh Breeze Guesthouse, a place full of stories. However, it seems that Kyou is avoiding Shingo...Pure feelings and immoral emotions blending together to form a sociogramatic LOVE.
name: Vol. 1

description: It's not my fault that he fell in love with me. On the day he entered College, Shingo reencounters his childhood friend Kyou. Shingo always desired to meet him once again, ever since the day Kyou mysteriously left home. He is accepted and moves in where Kyou lives-- Fresh Breeze Guesthouse, a place full of stories. However, it seems that Kyou is avoiding Shingo... Pure feelings and immoral emotions blend together to form a sociogramatic Love story in this final volume!!
name: Vol. 2

description:
Experience class Sherlock Holmes from the POV of his precocious niece!

Christie Holmes is a prodigy. At ten years old, she's as familiar with the sciences and classics as any older student at Cambridge or Oxford. And her facility with logic is reminiscent of her uncle, the eminent Sherlock Holmes himself. So, what's a brilliant young girl to do when her parents are away in India, leaving her behind in the care of maids and servants? Why, solve mysteries, of course.

Along with her giant hound Nelson, Christie's implacable curiosity leads her from one dangerous adventure to another, often joining forces with Uncle Sherlock and Doctor Watson on their famed investigations. Christie may look pint-sized, but her clever mind is never to be underestimated!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Experience classic Sherlock Holmes from the POV of his precocious niece!

Christie Holmes is a prodigy. At ten years old, she's as familiar with the sciences and classics as any older student at Cambridge or Oxford. And her facility with logic is reminiscent of her uncle, the eminent Sherlock Holmes himself. So, what's a brilliant young girl to do when her parents are away in India, leaving her behind in the care of maids and servants? Why, solve mysteries, of course.

Along with her giant hound Nelson, Christie's implacable curiosity leads her from one dangerous adventure to another, often joining forces with Uncle Sherlock and Doctor Watson on their famed investigations. Christie may look pint-sized, but her clever mind is never to be underestimated!

Christie's cases in this book include:

  • The Adventure of the Sussex Vampire
  • The Adventure of the Dancing Men
name: Vol. 2

description:
Crystal "Christie" Margaret Hope is back! This young lady is more at home in Scotland Yard's library than at a tea party, and more likely to ruffle feathers than to mind her manners. Join "Sherlock Holmes in miniature" for another round of adventures, and a deeper look into the history of those she holds dear, in this all-ages manga.

Christie, the precocious young niece of Sherlock Holmes, once again joins the famous Victorian detective and his sidekick Watson in tackling some of the strangest puzzles of all time. From a family haunted by a demon hound to a London vandal obsessed with smashing statues of Napoleon, no secrets are safe from Christie's curious mind - and no criminals are safe from her steadfast companions, the deceptively gentle Annmarie and the rambunctious Nora, not to mention her faithful hound Nelson (who sometimes doubles as her steed)!
name: Vol. 3

description: Each issue of Marvel Previews is a comic book-sized, 120-page, full-color guide and preview to all of Marvel's upcoming releases - it's your #1 source for advanced information on Marvel Comics! This October issue features items scheduled to ship in December 2013 and beyond.

As the angel Colopatiron continues to evade the angel hierarchy after losing the keys to Heaven, Mercy continues to be harassed as to his whereabouts. Meanwhile, how will the mysterious priest following Hank react when he sees Mercy Sparx in her true form?

List of covers and their creators:

ACover AMatt Merhoff1

RERetailer Exclusive Convention Cover?2

Featuring the ZvC debut of indie star creator Ray Friesen (Pirate Penguin vs. Ninja Chicken) and a new Becky & Bob adventure! Also, a new installment of Rich Koslowski's Death Valley High. Includes the second of the three Z-V-C puzzle variant covers!
Join the GD cast as they pull out the scary costumes, put up spooky decorations, play their choicest tricks and deliver their tastiest treats for another hit-filled Halloween!
name: The Green Pumpkin; Yum, Yum

description:
Arcana Comics and Simmons Comics Group are proud to present this special anthology, featuring the third chapters of Zipper, Dominatrix, and Gene Simmons' House of Horrors, as well as the third and final chapter of the first ever crossover between Zipper and Dominatrix, The Slave Trade!

Contents

  • Zipper Vs. Dominatrix - The Slave Trade - Chapter 3
  • Zipper - Chapter 3
  • Dominatrix - Chapter 3
  • Gene Simmons House of Horrors - Chapter 3
name: Volume 3

description: The Tin Man and his Emerald Army face off against Victoria and her unlikely allies. Do they stand a chance against the Emerald City's deadliest weapons? Surprises abound in the final chapter of the first arc in this epic SteamPunk re-imagining of Oz. Who joins in the fray and whatever happened to Scarecrow? Secrets will be revealed and loyalties tested. Who will be left standing in the end?
Dr. Harding gets to stretch his legs, Beta learns more about Ina Britt, and Dr. Vega reflects on the past.

Enjoy the early adventures of Heroic Publishing's beautiful scarlet-tressed occult detective, PSYCHE. These classic tales include the stories that appeared in Marksman #1-5, Rose #1-3, and Champions Adventures #7.

Story Titles

  • Ghost Story
  • The Return of Doctor Death
  • The Mystery of Brother Basilisk
  • With A Little Help From A Friend
  • And the Dark Man Laughed
  • The Bane of the Moor
  • Hellfire & malice
  • Dark Passion
  • Dark Passion, Part Two
  • Dark Passion, Chapter Three
name: Vol. 1

description:
Flare's electric little sister sparkles in this trade paperback collection of her classic solo adventures from the pages of Champions and Flare.

Story Titles

  • Freedom's Just Another Word
  • Olga's Flowers
  • The Ransom of Olga Gottmann
  • Flowers For My Hero
  • Buzz Off!
  • Menace of the Barkmeister
  • Trick Or Treat
  • Jimmy Dooley, Man of Wonder
  • A Sound of Distant Wonder
  • Perceptions
  • A Singular Repentance
name: Volume 1

description: In these stories from THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD #123-145 and 147-151, Batman teams up with The Flash, Aquaman, Mister Miracle, Green Arrow, Wonder Woman, Deadman, Green Lantern, Hawkman, The Phantom Stranger, Supergirl, the Teen Titans-and Jim Aparo himself!
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Legends of The Dark Knight: Jim Aparo

description: Collecting MARVEL UNIVERSE ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #13-16.
name: Volume 4

description: In 1992, legendary writer and artist Todd McFarlane unleashed his iconic antihero, Spawn, on the world. In so doing, he launched the most successful independent comic book in history - and the world would never be the same. Spawn: Origins Volume 19 trade paperback features the stories and artwork that helped cement the Spawn legacy. Relive the excitement of this groundbreaking series-collected in this accessibly priced format with exclusive bonus content, including cover galleries, b/w art, classic quotes from Todd McFarlane and an exclusive digitally painted cover by Clayton Crain. Collects SPAWN #111-116.
name: Volume 19

description: Miguel O'Hara, the friendly neighborhood Spider-Man of the year 2099, returns! When Spider-Man clashes with the Public Eye, he finds himself at a disadvantage - but is suddenly saved by the mysterious Thanatos. Has Downtown found a new hero, or does Thanatos have a more sinister agenda? And what is his connection to the mysterious Net Prophet, who arrives in 2099 through a portal from a strange and new universe? When Thanatos reveals his true colors, Spider-Man must battle for survival in a virtual unreality world! Plus: who is Mutagen, and why is he targeting people born with genetic impurities? And Miguel has his hands full when he battles a body-controlling virus, investigates a century-old Soviet submarine and faces the explosive Chernobyl! Collecting SPIDER-MAN 2099 #11-14 and ANNUAL #1, and material from 2099 UNLIMITED #1-3.
name: Volume Two

description: Don't miss a moment of the action from the 2012 5-issue miniseries as Wonder Woman must stop an attack on Themyscira, Batgirl falls into Duela Dent's trap, Supergirl and Power Girl confront a space invasion and much more!
name: Volume 1

description: Marvel's epic DARK TOWER saga concludes! The mentally handicapped young Sheemie possesses the power to shatter the very Beams of the Dark Tower - the fulcrum of existence itself. But Sheemie doesn't want to destroy reality. Imprisoned at Devar-Toi, all he wants is to be rescued. Roland Deschain is coming for him, but can Sheemie survive animal-headed guards and the monstrous Great Old Ones? Plus: In the Desatoya Mountains, Roland finds a haunted camp and relives a past adventure during which he and his ka-tet were trapped by supernatural enemies. How did the young Gunslinger survive the sinister assault? Finally, how does the Gunslinger's quest echo the legendary battle between a young Arthur Eld and a towering Lord Perth? Find out here! Collecting DARK TOWER: THE GUNSLINGER - SHEEMIE'S TALE #1-2, EVIL GROUND #1-2 and SO FELL LORD PERTH #1.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Dark Tower: The Gunslinger - Last Shots

description: Red She-Hulk is S.H.I.E.L.D.'s most wanted, and Machine Man has joined her on a deadly chase across the Marvel Universe! But Jennifer Walters, the original She-Hulk, is hot on their trail! Red She-Hulk goes deep underground to find the secrets of the ancient order of the Shield - but there's a new ruler of the world below, and he may never let her leave! As Jen Walters strikes a deal with the military, Red She-Hulk discovers others have also taken the path before her. Others named Dr. Doom, the Red Skull, Ultron and Loki! Is Red destined to become a villain, as well, or can she prevail in her race against time? And as she faces Man-Thing and Mad Thinker's retooled Echelon Super-Soldiers, will humanity pay the price for her interference in the future? Collecting RED SHE-HULK #63-67.
name: Volume 2

description: The biggest event of 2012 is now the biggest and boldest WHAT IF? event yet! We all know what happened between the Avengers and the X-Men when the Phoenix Force returned to Earth, but what if the story had gone differently? The one and only Jimmy Palmiotti brings his signature style to a mind-blowing reinterpretation of a key event in the history of the Marvel Universe! Featuring Magneto, Hope and every Avenger and X-Man you can imagine - and then some! Don't miss out! Collecting WHAT IF? AVX #1-4.
name: TPB

description: The Children of the Atom meet the Mitey 'Vengers in this giant-sized collection of pint-sized super heroics! There's no pacifying Cyclops and Cap, who swap 'ABC' for 'AVX' as the playground becomes a battleground over a cherished teddy bear! Then, when Mojo kidnaps Wolverine to star in his arena of death, it's Longshot, Dazzler and the uncannily cute X-Babies to the rescue! And when these junior X-Men stand up to the Brotherhood of Mutant Bullies in a murderous game show produced by Mojo and Arcade, will they be outdone by new kids on the block - or will one of their number dissolve back into the neoplasm from which they were formed? Plus: a gallery of Skottie Young's ever-adorable Marvel NOW! variant covers! Collecting A-BABIES VS. X-BABIES #1, WOLVERINE (1988) #102.5, PINT-SIZED X-BABIES: MURDERAMA and X-BABIES REBORN.
name: TPB

volume.name: Young Marvel: Little X-Men/Little Avengers Big Trouble

description: A dragon comes to River Heights, and the Clue Crew is on the case! Pre-teen detective Nancy Drew and her best friends Bess and George have seen a lot while solving mysteries in River Heights. But none of them have ever met a dragon before! When the exotic pet mysteriously appears on their teacher's desk, the Clue Crew have to discover where it came from, how to get it back home, and most importantly, how to take care of it in the meantime. Available in softcover and hardcover editions.
name: Enter the Dragon Mystery

volume.name: Nancy Drew and the Clue Crew

description: Based off the New York Times best selling novels. The Iron King is the first book in the Iron Fey series, and follows the adventures of a girl named Meghan Chase. On her sixteenth birthday, Meghan discovers her little brother has been kidnapped by a faery race known as "the Fey" and even worse, replaced with an evil changeling and taken into the "Nevernever." Meghan bravely ventures into the faery realm to rescue him, and that's where an epic plot unfolds.

Can't Lose You is the story of two characters who come from opposite worlds but are united by the most unlikely of circumstances: Yooi is a desperate girl working day and night to earn pennies in hopes of one day paying off her father's debts and reuniting their family. Lida comes from privilege and excess, the heiress to an unbelievable fortune and a marriage match she cannot wait to consummate. The two girls meet and discover that they have identical faces. As Yooi accepts the irresistible offer of becoming Lida's look-alike, she finds herself in over her head, being chased by assassins and falling head over heels for Lida's fiancé. A revelation of social boundaries and emotional limitlessness, this story will have your heart beating faster with every turn of the page.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Doppelganger
  • Chapter 2: Gil, Gaon
  • Chapter 3: The Double
  • Chapter 4: A Crisis
  • Chapter 5: Immersion
  • Chapter 6: A Bait
name: Vol. 1
